<Link id="l00436" /><CodeLine lineNumber="436"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00437" /><CodeLine lineNumber="437"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Extend the generic ELFStreamer class so that it can emit mapping symbols at</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00438" /><CodeLine lineNumber="438"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the appropriate points in the object files. These symbols are defined in the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00439" /><CodeLine lineNumber="439"><Highlight kind="comment">/// ARM ELF ABI: infocenter.arm.com/help/topic/com.arm.../IHI0044D&#95;aaelf.pdf.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00440" /><CodeLine lineNumber="440"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00441" /><CodeLine lineNumber="441"><Highlight kind="comment">/// In brief: $a, $t or $d should be emitted at the start of each contiguous</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00442" /><CodeLine lineNumber="442"><Highlight kind="comment">/// region of ARM code, Thumb code or data in a section. In practice, this</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00443" /><CodeLine lineNumber="443"><Highlight kind="comment">/// emission does not rely on explicit assembler directives but on inherent</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00444" /><CodeLine lineNumber="444"><Highlight kind="comment">/// properties of the directives doing the emission (e.g. &quot;.byte&quot; is data, &quot;add</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00445" /><CodeLine lineNumber="445"><Highlight kind="comment">/// r0, r0, r0&quot; an instruction).</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00446" /><CodeLine lineNumber="446"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00447" /><CodeLine lineNumber="447"><Highlight kind="comment">/// As a result this system is orthogonal to the DataRegion infrastructure used</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00448" /><CodeLine lineNumber="448"><Highlight kind="comment">/// by MachO. Beware!</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00449" /><CodeLine lineNumber="449" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-armelfstreamer-cpp-/armelfstreamer"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">class </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-armelfstreamer-cpp-/armelfstreamer/#a039b5e6ab81cb5875ca14bf9359570d2">ARMELFStreamer</a> : </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">public</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcelfstreamer/#aec09c5b9322b90f034d51bd3c0903563">MCELFStreamer</a> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
